	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />You must have checked before NTFS-3G came out.  Since then, NTFS on Linux has been full read/write.  I think the Ubuntu or Knoppix liveCDs may even automount NTFS as read/write now, but I'm not sure about that.  If they don't, you just need to manually mount it.
<br />I do know they refuse to write to an NTFS volume marked as "Dirty" to encourage you to run chkdsk on it before you mess with it, but you can still override that.

		

